  "short_text": "Minimum of Two Numbers",
  "content": "Write a program that reads two integers `a` and `b` and uses shorthand if-else to print the smaller of the given two numbers.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nA line containing two integers, `a` and `b`, separated by space.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output is the smaller of the two integers.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the input is:\n\n```\n5 10\n```\n\nThe output should be:\n\n```\n5\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "b92fad6c-7910-41fe-a008-c242fa18af93",
      "code_content": "inp = input().split()\na = int(inp[0])\nb = int(inp[1])\nprint(a if a < b else b)",
